tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a full aesthetic overhaul, moving
  from a generic look to a calming, professional, and cohesive sleep-themed
  design. This included a new color palette, redesigned layouts, polished UI
  components, and consistent styling across all sections, along with a bug fix
  for input values.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic redesign for their sleep
  questionnaire app, aiming for a more polished and professional look. The
  process began with an in-depth analysis of existing styles, leading to the
  implementation of a new sleep-themed color palette, refined main form layouts
  with subtle background effects, and enhanced core UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. The introduction and report sections
  were significantly updated with thematic elements and consistent styling. A
  minor bug related to null input values was also addressed. Following user
  feedback, a second round of improvements focused on unifying alert styles
  across the app using custom utility classes and ensuring all section groupings
  and report card headers adhered to the new sleep theme, replacing previous
  inconsistent color choices. The outcome is a visually cohesive, calming, and
  professional application experience.
